defaultExecutive Summarydefault&#xa0;
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultHeartbeat, an international NGO based in Jerusalem, unites Israeli and Palestinian youth to build trust and transform conflict through music and popular media.
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWorking to overcome the segregation that fuels the Israeli and Palestinian conflict, Heartbeat 
defaultdevelops ensembles of young Arab and Jewish musicians (ages 14-23 years old) who come together weekly for sustained music based dialogue programs in cities throughout the region. Heartbeat youth musicians bring their recordings, music videos, and performan
defaultces to their communities in an attempt to build trust, share understanding, inspire hope, and engage more people in taking responsibility for the future.
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultLess than 1% of the Israeli and Palestinian populations has had a meaningful positive interaction wi
defaultth someone from the other side.  While extremism and violence dictate public opinion, the vast silent majority of peace seeking citizens on both sides is largely unheard and so remains unaware of partners for peace on the other side.   Without contact, dis
defaulttrust persists and so the cycles of discrimination, violence, poverty, and political instability continue throughout the region.
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe United Kingdom’s extremely valuable contributions to the Middle East in the areas of education, health, poverty alleviatio
defaultn, care for refugees and security hold limited impact without addressing the root cause of these issues: the ongoing distrust between Israelis and Palestinians.
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultPeople-to-people diplomacy, particularly amongst youth, is the proven and necessary tool to bu
defaultild trust between Palestinians and Israelis and therefore to establish the foundation for a lasting peace for Israelis, Palestinians, and all of their neighbours.
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultOver 100 organisations, including Heartbeat, work tirelessly to empower Israeli and Palestin
defaultian citizens to build peace from the ground up.  Heartbeat encourages the Parliament, the DFID, and the 
defaultBritish Interdepartmental Conflict Pool
default to make people to people diplomacy a central tenant in its Middle East policy by increasing its investment in th
defaulte work of these organisations, particularly those who offer participants a sustained, long-term, encounter experience with a common goal. 
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultHeartbeat invites the UK to become a principle investor in the International Fund for Israeli-Palestinian Peace (mod
defaulteled after the International Fund for Northern Ireland), which seeks to establish a $200 million (USD) annual fund to support joint Israeli-Palestinian initiatives.
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultOrganizational Overviewdefault&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultHeartbeat, an international NGO based in Jerusalem, unites Israeli
default and Palestinian youth to harness the tools of music and popular media to build trust and transform conflict.  Working to overcome the segregation that fuels the Israeli-Palestinian conflict, Heartbeat
default creates spaces for young Palestinian and Israeli music
defaultians to work together, develop creative non-violent tools to build trust, understanding and 
defaultrespect, and provides youth with opportunities to amplify their voices and positively influence their communities.
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultHeartbeat’s core program focuses on the 
defaultestablishment and facilitation of ensembles of young Arab and Jewish musicians (ages 14-23 years old) who come together weekly for sustained music based dialogue programs in Jerusalem, Haifa, and Jaffa. During these weekly sessions, Heartbeat youth explore
default each other’s cultures and narratives in safe, politically neutral settings that support creativity and communication. Developing skills in improvisation, song-writing, performance technique, music theory, communication, and leadership while engaging in di
defaultalogue about their daily lives and the conflict, participants raise their critical consciousness, and harness their agency to transform the conflict between their communities.  When ready, Heartbeat youth musicians bring their recordings, music videos, and
default performances to their communities in an attempt to build trust, share understanding, inspire hope, and engage more people in taking responsibility for the future.
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultReason for Submitting Evidencedefault&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultHeartbeat recognises the transformative power that the Unit
defaulted Kingdom holds, should it choose to fully invest in addressing the root cause of the Israeli-Palestinian conflict and ending the Israeli-Palestinian conflict once and for all.  Undoubtedly, the UK’s remarkable and at times vital contributions in the area
defaults of education, health, poverty alleviation, care for refugees and security play an important role in promoting a sustainable future for the region.  Sadly, each of these areas remains in a perilous state due to the ongoing instability caused by decades of
default sectarian conflict.  To address each of these issues in the most pragmatic and effective manner, one must begin by addressing the root causes underlying the issues: the ongoing distrust between Israelis and Palestinians.
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultHeartbeat submits this testimony 
defaultto call attention to the severely under-utilized potential of people-to-people diplomacy, particularly amongst youth, as the proven tool to build trust between Palestinians and Israelis and to establish the foundation for a lasting peace for Israelis, Pale
defaultstinians, and all of their neighbours.
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultTo end the Israeli-Palestinian conflict, a critical mass of Israelis and Palestinians must come to trust one another.  The only thing separating today’s reality from this goal is funding. 
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultHeartbeat encourages the U
defaultK to become a principle investor in the International Fund for Israeli-Palestinian Peace, which seeks to establish a $200 million (USD) annual fund to support joint Israeli-Palestinian initiatives.
default&#xa0;
